# Default: any file Git auto-detects as text is normalized to LF in the repo
# and in the working tree, regardless of the cloner's core.autocrlf setting.
# Git for Windows defaults to core.autocrlf=true, which otherwise rewrites
# text files to CRLF on checkout and breaks bash, cmake, and make on Cygwin
# and MSYS.
#
# This is a no-op on Linux and macOS — those checkouts are already LF and
# stay LF. Binary file types (sysouts, fonts, .LCOM, .DFASL, .TEDIT, .SKETCH,
# etc.) are declared in medley/.gitattributes and remain untouched.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders: explicit overrides for shell scripts and make
# fragments, in case Git's auto-detection misclassifies any of them.
*.sh            text eol=lf
*.bash          text eol=lf
*.command       text eol=lf
*.mk            text eol=lf
*.pl            text eol=lf

Makefile        text eol=lf
makefile-*      text eol=lf
